article.headline: IPFW 68, N. Dakota St. 59
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Ben Botts scored 19 points and Trey McCorkle added 10 points and 13 rebounds as IPFW pulled away from North Dakota State late for a 68-59 victory Saturday night. Nick Daniels had 13 points and Zach Plackemeier 12 for the Mastodons (9-10, 4-5 Summit). Eric Carlson led the Bison (6-12, 3-5) with 23 points, and Michael Tveidt had 14. IPFW trailed 58-57 with 4:04 to play before scoring seven straight points en route to ending the game on an 11-1 run. Both teams shot poorly -- IPFW 39.7 percent, NDSU 39.3 percent -- but the Mastodons took advantage of 12 turnovers by the Bison, turning them into 17 points. IPFW led 51-43 with 11:33 to play before NDSU scored six unanswered points to pull within two. The Bison later went on a 9-2 run to take a 58-57 advantage. A 3 by Plackemeier at the end of the first half put IPFW ahead 37-32.
